JOHANNESBURG - Mining production increased year on year in March, while manufacturing slowed in the first quarter.The latest numbers from Stats SA show manufacturing decreased 0.9 percent in the first quarter, compared with the previous one.READ: GDP: Fall in mining production puts SA economy in slumpSeven of the 10 manufacturing divisions reported negative growth rates, due to lacklustre demand.By contrast, mining production data has come in better than expected.Production increased dramatically by 15.5 percent year on year in March.The biggest contributors were platinum - up 30 percent - iron ore and coal. Many are predicting that the sector will make a positive contribution to first-quarter GDP. iNet Bridge